The co-founder, chairman, and ex-CEO of Apple, Jobs introduced the iPhone, which is one of the most sought after devices globally. Now, one of the Jobs’ personally used items is going under the hammer and you’ll be shocked to know how much it costs.
The auction is being hosted by Julien's Auctions. According to the description on the website, a pair of brown suede leather Birkenstock Arizona sandals that Steve Jobs owned and used are up for sale. The estimate of the pair of unique sandals is $60,000 and $80,000 ( approximately Rs 48,32,889- Rs 64,43,852).

